title: Emily Hatch Resume
text:
Computer Information Technology

ehatche@gmail.com linkedin.com/in/emily-hatch-byui



Pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in Computer Information Technology with hands-on experience in programming, networking, and technical problem-solving.


Python, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, C#, SQL, AWS, GitHub, Unreal Engine (C++/Shaders)



Software engineering, network systems, cybersecurity, game development, cloud technologies.




Expected Apr. 2026
Brigham Young University – Idaho, Rexburg, ID
- B.S. in Computer Information Technology
- Certification: CompTIA Security+
- Classroom experience with Python, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, C#, SQL, AWS, GitHub



Apr. 2025 – Sept. 2025
Baker, Jacob Lake Inn — Fredonia, AZ
May 2024 – Aug. 2024
Applied Tech Intern, Dimension Studios — London, UK
- Completed technical projects involving C++ and shader coding in Unreal Engine
- Demonstrated independence and resourcefulness
- Collaborated effectively both online and in person
Nov. 2021 – May 2023
Full-Time Volunteer, The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints — Ogden, UT
- Worked 70-hour weeks while serving in leadership roles, including trainer for new volunteers
- Became fluent in American Sign Language and taught it to others
Aug. 2021 – Nov. 2021
Emissions Compliance Intern, PACCAR — Bellevue, WA
- Reviewed and developed certification processes aligned with EPA and CARB requirements
- Studied naming structures, labeling, and serialization processes
- Compiled regulatory information into presentations for Senior Management




Hackathon Volunteer: supported logistics and event operations

Experienced with Cisco Packet Tracer and physical networking equipment

Strong communication and teamwork skills

Technical writing and presentation experience



Last updated: December 2025
